vistra.framework.graph

Class TraversableGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.GraphDecorator<IVertex,IEdge>
      • vistra.framework.graph.TraversableGraph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.Graph<IVertex,IEdge>, edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.Hypergraph<IVertex,IEdge>, java.io.Serializable, ITraversableGraph

    public class TraversableGraph
extends edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.GraphDecorator<IVertex,IEdge>
implements ITraversableGraph
    A traversable graph. The graph delegates most of its method calls to a constructor-specified Graph.
    • Modifiers are not supported anymore: vertices and edges can neither been added nor removed.
    • In addition, this graph serves with 'step'-methods which an IAlgorithm-developer can use for traversing over the graph and generating steps of a Traversal.
    Author:
    Roland Bruggmann (brugr9@bfh.ch)
    See Also:
    IAlgorithm, ITraversal, IStep, Serialized Form
